# 🛠️ DevOps Engineer — Complete Task Guide for IoT Platform

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This guide extracts **every task that falls on the DevOps engineer** from the IoT Platform Definitive Guide. The project is a **5-week graduate course project** and the codebase is currently **empty** (only placeholder READMEs exist). Your work underpins everything the developers build.

---

## 📌 Your Scope at a Glance

As the DevOps engineer, you own **6 major domains**:

| # | Domain | Guide Parts |
|---|--------|------------|
| 1 | **Project Structure & Repository Setup** | Part 12 |
| 2 | **CI/CD Pipeline** (GitHub Actions + GHCR) | Part 10 |
| 3 | **Kubernetes Deployment** (Kustomize, namespaces, manifests) | Part 9 |
| 4 | **Infrastructure Services** (Kafka, PostgreSQL, InfluxDB, MongoDB) | Parts 3, 9 |
| 5 | **Observability & Monitoring** (Prometheus, Grafana, Alertmanager) | Part 11 |
| 6 | **Security Hardening** (secrets, network policies, non-root containers) | Part 8 |

---

## 🗓️ Week-by-Week DevOps Tasks

### Week 1 — Foundation

| # | Task | Details | Deliverable |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 1 | **Create GitHub repo with full project structure** | See [File Structure](#-task-1-project-file-structure) below | All directories and placeholder files exist |
| 2 | **Set up CI workflow** | GitHub Actions: `ruff` + `pytest` on every push/PR for Python services; `eslint` + `vitest` for frontend | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` green on push |
| 3 | **Deploy infrastructure on local K8s** | minikube or k3s: **Kafka** (3 replicas, Strimzi, KRaft mode), **PostgreSQL 16**, **InfluxDB 2.7**, **MongoDB 7** | All 4 infra services running, accessible from pods |
| 4 | **Create Kafka topics** | `iot.telemetry` (6 partitions, 7d retention), `iot.commands` (3 partitions, 1d), `iot.device-events` (3 partitions, 3d), `iot.cmd-responses` (3 partitions, 1d) | Topics created and verified |
| 5 | **PostgreSQL schema init** | Apply the SQL from Part 6 (tables: `users`, `groups`, `devices`, `device_credentials`, `user_tokens` + indexes) | Schema migration script or init SQL |
| 6 | **Write Dockerfiles** | Multi-stage Dockerfiles for: `iot-backend`, `pubsub-broker`, `telemetry-worker`, `ttl-cleanup-worker`, `web-app` | Each service builds and runs in Docker |

### Week 2 — Broker Infrastructure

| # | Task | Details | Deliverable |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 7 | **K8s manifests for broker** | `pubsub-broker/` StatefulSet (2 replicas), LoadBalancer Service on TCP `:1883` | ESP32 can reach broker via external IP |
| 8 | **K8s manifests for telemetry-worker** | Deployment (3 replicas), env vars for Kafka + InfluxDB + MongoDB | Workers consuming from Kafka |
| 9 | **K8s manifest for TTL cleanup worker** | CronJob running hourly | CronJob scheduled and tested |
| 10 | **ConfigMaps and Secrets** | ConfigMap: DB URLs, Kafka bootstrap, InfluxDB org/bucket. Secrets: DB passwords, JWT secret, Kafka creds | All config externalized |

### Week 3 — CI/CD Pipeline & Staging

| # | Task | Details | Deliverable |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 11 | **Complete CI pipeline** | Matrix job: lint + test per service, Docker build + push to GHCR (tagged with commit SHA), Trivy security scan | Fully automated CI |
| 12 | **CD pipeline — staging** | On merge to `main`: Kustomize sets image tags → kubectl apply to staging → wait for rollout → integration tests | Auto-deploy to staging |
| 13 | **Kustomize base manifests** | All base manifests complete (see structure below) | `k8s/base/` complete |
| 14 | **Kustomize staging overlay** | 1 replica per service, staging domain | `k8s/overlays/staging/` |
| 15 | **Ingress configuration** | Nginx Ingress: `/` → web-app, `/api` → iot-backend | External routing works |

### Week 4 — Integration & Hardening

| # | Task | Details | Deliverable |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 16 | **Integration test infrastructure** | pytest + httpx test suite running against staging | `tests/integration/` |
| 17 | **Full K8s manifests verified** | All 9 components deployed and communicating | End-to-end data flow working |
| 18 | **PVC verification** | PostgreSQL: 10Gi, InfluxDB: 20Gi, MongoDB: 10Gi | Data persists across pod restarts |

### Week 5 — Production & Monitoring

| # | Task | Details | Deliverable |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 19 | **Production Kustomize overlay** | 2-3 replicas, higher resource limits, TLS via cert-manager, production domain | `k8s/overlays/production/` |
| 20 | **Manual approval gate** | GitHub environment protection rule on `production` environment | Merge to main → staging auto → approval → prod |
| 21 | **Prometheus metrics + ServiceMonitors** | Scrape all services for metrics listed below | `monitoring/service-monitors.yaml` |
| 22 | **Grafana dashboards** | Pre-built dashboards for API latency, Kafka lag, broker connections, TTL cleanup | `monitoring/grafana-dashboards.json` |
| 23 | **Alertmanager rules** | 5 alert rules (see below) | `monitoring/alertmanager-config.yaml` |
| 24 | **Network policies** | Restrict pod-to-pod communication per namespace | Isolation enforced |
| 25 | **Security hardening** | Non-root containers, read-only root filesystem, sealed-secrets | All containers hardened |
| 26 | **Deployment guide document** | Step-by-step deployment instructions | `docs/deployment-guide.md` |

