## 📊 Task 21-23: Monitoring & Alerts

### Prometheus Metrics to Collect

| Metric | Source Service |
|--------|---------------|
| `http_requests_total{method, path, status}` | IoT backend |
| `http_request_duration_seconds` | IoT backend |
| `telemetry_consumer_lag{partition}` | Telemetry worker |
| `broker_active_connections` | Broker gateway |
| `ttl_cleanup_duration_seconds` | TTL cleanup worker |
| `ttl_cleanup_points_deleted{group_id}` | TTL cleanup worker |

### Alert Rules

| Alert | Condition | Severity |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| `HighAPIErrorRate` | 5xx rate > 5% for 5 min | 🔴 Critical |
| `TelemetryConsumerLag` | lag > 1000 for 3 min | 🟡 Warning |
| `PodCrashLooping` | > 3 restarts in 15 min | 🔴 Critical |
| `BrokerNoConnections` | 0 connections for 2 min | 🟡 Warning |
| `TTLCleanupFailed` | 3 consecutive CronJob failures | 🟡 Warning |

---

## 🔒 Task 24-25: Security Hardening Checklist

- [ ] All DB passwords, JWT secret, Kafka creds in **K8s Secrets** (sealed-secrets for prod)
- [ ] Internal endpoints (`/internal/*`) **NOT** exposed via Ingress
- [ ] All containers run as **non-root** (`USER appuser` in Dockerfile)
- [ ] **Read-only root filesystem** (`securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true`)
- [ ] **Network Policies** restrict pod-to-pod communication:
  - `iot-app` pods → can reach `iot-infra` (PostgreSQL, InfluxDB, MongoDB) + Kafka
  - `iot-broker` pods → can reach `iot-infra` (Kafka, PostgreSQL) + `iot-app` (internal API)
  - `iot-infra` pods → only accept connections from `iot-app` and `iot-broker`
- [ ] Trivy image scanning in CI (blocks on HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs)
- [ ] TLS for Ingress via **cert-manager** (production overlay)

